reme=\r\n happiness is gained via contentment.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-weight:bol=\r\nd&quot;&gt;2.54 When the mind maintains awareness, yet does not mingle with the sen=\r\nses, nor the senses with sense impressions, then self-awareness blossoms.&lt;/=\r\nspan&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n\n\n\n\n\n&lt;br&gt;2.55 In this way comes mastery over the senses.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;=\r\nspan style=3D&quot;font-weight:bold&quot;&gt;Part Three on Divine Powers&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;3=\r\n.1 One-pointedness is steadfastness of the mind.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;3.2 Unbroken contin=\r\nuation of that mental ability is meditation.&lt;br&gt;\n\n\n\n\n\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;fo=\r\nnt-weight:bold&quot;&gt;3.3 That same meditation when there is only consciousness o=\r\nf the object of meditation and not of the mind is realization.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b=\r\nr&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-weight:bold&quot;&gt;Part Four on Realizations&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n\n\n\n=\r\n\n\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-weight:bold&quot;&gt;4.4 Created minds arise from egoism =\r\nalone.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-weight:bold&quot;&gt;4.27 Distractions ari=\r\nse from habitual thought patterns when practice is intermittent.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;=\r\n\n&lt;br&gt;4.34 When the attributes cease mutative association with awarenessness=\r\n, they resolve into dormancy in Nature, and the indweller shines forth as p=\r\nure consciousness. This is absolute freedom.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-wei=\r\nght:bold&quot;&gt;Source&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;a rel=3D&quot;nofollow&quot; href=3D&quot;http://www.celextel.or=\r\ng/othervedantabooks/patanjaliyogasutras.html&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://www.=\r\ncelextel.org/othervedantabooks/patanjaliyogasutras.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;div&gt;\n\n\n\n\n\n&lt;/div=\r\n&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;-- &lt;br&gt;=E0=B0=93=E0=B0=82=C2=A0 =E0=B0=A8=E0=B0=AE=E0=B1=8B=C2=\r\n=A0 =E0=B0